public of China: evolution, structure and reform.\" ''International Nursing Review'' 47.4 (2000): 207-217. [https://pdfs.semanticscholar.org/1131/a3d964f37082ebd6b0982a4bd5c30a77a745.pdf online]\n\n====India====\n\n* {{cite book|author=Healey, Madelaine|title=Indian Sisters: A History of Nursing Leadership and the State, 1907\u20132007|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=AHo9BAAAQBAJ&pg=PP1|year=2014|publisher=Routledge|isbn=978-1-317-56009-8}}\n\n===Europe===\n* McFarland-Icky, Bronny Rebekah. ''Nurses in Nazi Germany'' (Princeton University Press, 1999)\n* Rafferty, Anne Marie. \"Tiptoeing towards a history of nursing in Europe\" ''Nursing history review: official journal of the American Association for the History of Nursing'' 22 (2013): 107\u2013113.\n\n[[Category:History of nursing| ]]\n[[Category:Catholic nursing orders]]\n", "name_user": "Kahtar", "label": "safe", "comment": "Repair CS1 error(s), replaced: website=www. \u2192 website=", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/History_of_nursing"}
{"title_page": "Lillian (film)", "text_new": "{{short description|2019 film}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=April 2020}}\n{{Infobox film\n| name           = Lillian\n| image          = Lillian (film).jpg\n| caption        = Film poster\n| director       = [[Andreas Horvath]]\n| producer       = \n| writer         = Andreas Horvath\n| starring       = [[Patrycja Planik]]\n| music          = Andreas Horvath\n| cinematography = Andreas Horvath\n| editing        = Michael Palm<br>Andreas Horvath\n| distributor    = \n| released       = {{film date|2019|5|20|[[2019 Cannes Film Festival|Cannes]]|df=yes}}\n| runtime        = 130 minutes\n| country        = Austria\n| language       = English\n}}\n\n'''''Lillian''''' is a 2019 Austrian [[drama film]] directed by [[Andreas Horvath]]. It was screened in the [[Directors' Fortnight]] section at the [[2019 Cannes Film Festival]].<ref>{{cite web |last1=Keslassy |first1=Elsa |title=Cannes: ''Deerskin'' With Jean Dujardin to Open Directors' Fortnight |url=https://variety.com/2019/film/news/cannes-deerskin-with-jean-dujardin-to-open-directors-fortnight-1203180491/ |website=Variety |accessdate=19 April 2019 |language=en |date=4 April 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last1=Goodfellow |first1=Melanie |title=Cannes Directors' Fortnight unveils genre-heavy 2019 selection |url=https://www.screendaily.com/news/cannes-directors-fortnight-unveils-genre-heavy-2019-selection/5138683.article |website=ScreenDaily |accessdate=23 April 2019}}</ref>\n\n==Cast==\n* [[Patrycja Planik]] as Lillian\n\n[[File:Actress Patrycja Planik, at the presentation ceremony of film \u2018Lillian\u2019, during the 50th International Film Festival of India (IFFI-2019), in Panaji, Goa on November 28, 2019.jpg|thumb|left|Patrycja Planik, receiving the award for the film during [[International Film Festival of India|IFFI]] ([[50th International Film Festival of India|2019]])]]{{clear}}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{IMDb title|10244754|Lillian}}\n\n{{DEFAU